tt-bio — vendored third-party model artifacts
============================================

This directory ships small reference artifacts for the standalone affinity
head port (PLAPT-style). Per-file provenance and licenses:

  head_weights.npz
    Weights of the PLAPT affinity predictor MLP, extracted from
    `affinity_predictor.onnx` (Bindwell/PLAPT, MIT License, Copyright (c) 2024
    Bindwell). See `LICENSE-PLAPT` for the full MIT text. The extraction
    preserves the ONNX initializers verbatim (no retraining); the original
    PLAPT code is at https://github.com/Bindwell/PLAPT .

  chemberta/
    Tokenizer + config files for `seyonec/ChemBERTa-zinc-base-v1` (MIT License,
    ChemBERTa by Seyonec). The model weights (pytorch_model.bin, ~178 MB) are
    NOT vendored here — they are fetched at runtime from HuggingFace by
    `tt_bio.affinity.ChemBERTa.from_pretrained`. Only config.json, vocab.json,
    merges.txt, and the tokenizer-config files are vendored (a few KB total).

The from-scratch PyTorch reference for parity testing lives in
`tests/affinity_reference.py` (no `transformers` dependency).
